headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball had 26 points, nine assists and eight rebounds, and the Charlotte Hornets routed the short-handed Orlando Magic 128-101 on Thursday night to get back on the right track after two lopsided losses.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball leads Hornets past Magic after 3 players ejected

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 37 points, 12 assists and 11 rebounds for his third career triple-double, Gary Trent Jr. scored 30 points and the Toronto Raptors beat the Philadelphia 76ers 119-114 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pascal Siakam has triple-double, Raptors beat 76ers 119-114

headlines.description: — The Milwaukee Bucks turned up their defensive intensity just in time Thursday night to beat the short-handed Boston Celtics and take over second place in the Eastern Conference standings.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis, Holiday help Bucks rally past Celtics 127-121

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards set a career high with 49 points and Karl-Anthony Towns had 21 points and 13 rebounds as the Minnesota Timberwolves hung on for a 127-121 win over the San Antonio Spurs on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards scores 49 as Timberwolves hold off Spurs, 127-121

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic made history on the night his Denver Nuggets clinched a fourth consecutive playoff berth with a 122-109 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nuggets clinch playoff berth with 122-109 rout of Grizzlies

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Golden State coach Steve Kerr made a point to tell Klay Thompson he played his best game yet since returning in January from a 2 1/2-year absence following surgeries and long rehabs on his left knee and right Achilles.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thompson scores 33, Warriors beat Lakers to win third in row
